1
00:00:05,930 --> 00:00:07,763
In the past,

2
00:00:07,763 --> 00:00:12,718
I used to think that people's lives were like a fun video game.

3
00:00:17,946 --> 00:00:20,441
Before we could pass each stage,

4
00:00:20,442 --> 00:00:23,690
there's a chance that we could die over and over,

5
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:27,794
and then we'd be granted a new life to start again

6
00:00:29,066 --> 00:00:32,258
So I had never thought about death before.

7
00:00:32,258 --> 00:00:36,958
Even though the fact is, life is not like in a game

8
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:39,434
because people can only die once.

9
00:00:40,922 --> 00:00:45,374
So why is it that people are never willing to think about death?

10
00:00:46,950 --> 00:00:51,902
Have you ever imagined how you would die?

11
00:00:51,902 --> 00:00:55,990
Or have you ever thought for fun, what it would be like...

12
00:00:55,990 --> 00:01:01,965
if you were lucky and had a second life like in video games?

13
00:01:05,450 --> 00:01:06,983
Yes!

14
00:01:17,098 --> 00:01:18,998
No hard feelings, Buddy.

15
00:01:27,810 --> 00:01:29,526
-Hey, you guys. Let's go.
- Let's go.

16
00:01:29,526 --> 00:01:30,959
Wait.

17
00:01:31,950 --> 00:01:34,442
I think this game should be more fun though.

18
00:01:49,178 --> 00:01:50,711
You afraid?

19
00:01:52,470 --> 00:01:53,801
Wait...

20
00:01:53,802 --> 00:01:55,799
What the hell are you doing, dude?

21
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,300
Your mom just gave that to you this year.

22
00:02:00,298 --> 00:02:02,098
That's not ordinary.

23
00:02:02,810 --> 00:02:04,860
Why be afraid?

24
00:02:04,860 --> 00:02:06,709
I'm going to die soon anyway.

25
00:02:06,710 --> 00:02:08,745
Once I'm dead I can't take it with me anyway, right?

26
00:02:08,746 --> 00:02:12,410
What? "Die"?

27
00:02:15,290 --> 00:02:18,505
It's just a joke. Why the hell are you being serious?

28
00:02:18,506 --> 00:02:19,593
Here's the deal.

29
00:02:19,594 --> 00:02:22,229
If I win against Ai' Pete,

30
00:02:22,230 --> 00:02:24,400
You guys can go ahead and share it all.

31
00:02:25,170 --> 00:02:28,169
Hey. It's not just for fun for me.

32
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:29,705
I'm taking them for real, alright?

33
00:02:29,706 --> 00:02:31,402
Then just go for it.

34
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:39,833
[Pa' Nim]

35
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:51,129
Hello, Pa'?

36
00:02:51,130 --> 00:02:53,870
Just what time are you going to arrive, Ee' Torfun?

37
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:56,869
Probably in about another hour maybe?

38
00:02:56,870 --> 00:02:58,689
The bus left later than scheduled.

39
00:02:58,689 --> 00:03:01,721
It's so late already! I've been waiting for you here!

40
00:03:01,722 --> 00:03:03,641
So how many days are you going to stay this time?

41
00:03:03,642 --> 00:03:05,222
Why don't you just move and work at the factory here?

42
00:03:05,222 --> 00:03:07,479
Help me earn some money already!

43
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,479
Well I send it to you every month, don't I?

44
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,630
And do you think that's enough then?

45
00:03:14,090 --> 00:03:15,656
For living expenses or expenses to play cards?

46
00:03:15,657 --> 00:03:17,000
Don't you dare lecture me.

47
00:03:17,001 --> 00:03:18,409
Just like your mom!

48
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:20,198
What? Auntie!

49
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:28,969
I'll take a cab home then. That's all for now, alright?

50
00:03:28,970 --> 00:03:31,114
Yeah, yeah! Hurry up already!

51
00:03:39,770 --> 00:03:43,058
Hey! Let's have a break. I'm drained.

52
00:03:43,058 --> 00:03:44,691
Keep it down!

53
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:53,746
Hey! Shit! Hide!

54
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:08,570
Gosh, I'm about to pass out watching this.

55
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:18,603
Go!

56
00:04:42,330 --> 00:04:44,230
No hard feelings, Buddy.

57
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:49,963
Wait, Buddy.

58
00:04:54,550 --> 00:04:57,366
I think this game isn't fun anymore.

59
00:04:57,366 --> 00:04:59,750
How about we continue playing on the road?

60
00:05:19,194 --> 00:05:20,827
Hey! Stop!

61
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:25,630
Throw away your weapon!

62
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:31,603
Slowly.

63
00:05:55,514 --> 00:05:56,697
Sure, Hia.

64
00:05:56,698 --> 00:05:58,940
But you've cleared the road for sure, right?

65
00:05:59,690 --> 00:06:03,014
Yes. If that's what you're saying, Hia, then I feel at ease.

66
00:06:03,014 --> 00:06:06,289
Go ahead and handle it, Hia. Thank you so much.

67
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:08,442
Hey, I'm going to go get my car first. See you on the road.

68
00:06:08,443 --> 00:06:10,153
- See you.
- See you.

69
00:06:10,154 --> 00:06:11,942
Of course. Of course.

70
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,309
Who is your boss?

71
00:06:34,309 --> 00:06:37,982
I told you everything already. That's all I know!

72
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:41,657
Say it!

73
00:06:41,658 --> 00:06:43,149
Speak! I told you to say it!

74
00:06:43,149 --> 00:06:44,583
Chief!

75
00:06:47,890 --> 00:06:51,442
Another guy...he's fled already.

76
00:06:55,482 --> 00:06:57,215
What should we do next?

77
00:07:03,018 --> 00:07:05,369
Send them to the border patrol police.

78
00:07:05,370 --> 00:07:06,473
Yes, sir.

79
00:07:06,474 --> 00:07:07,907
Get up!

80
00:07:08,538 --> 00:07:09,971
Go!

81
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,363
Damn it!

82
00:08:13,550 --> 00:08:19,200
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

83
00:08:56,130 --> 00:09:02,550
♫ The story that's been told however many times is still the same ♫

84
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:08,950
♫ It's that I love you, love you. It has never changed ♫

85
00:09:08,950 --> 00:09:15,540
♫ If perhaps the stars hear the words of the prayers within my heart ♫

86
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:26,030
♫ No matter how many thousands of times, I'll still ask for my heart to be near you ♫

87
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:29,600
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

88
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:36,470
[Chapter 1]

89
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:38,160
[Ambulance]

90
00:09:44,490 --> 00:09:46,250
[Ambulance | Bangpo General Hospital]

91
00:09:55,834 --> 00:09:57,481
Tian, my son! Tian!

92
00:09:57,482 --> 00:09:59,559
Tian, stay with Mom!

93
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:02,589
Tian! Stay with Mom, alright, Tian?

94
00:10:02,589 --> 00:10:04,158
-Honey! Honey!
-Tian! Tian!

95
00:10:08,454 --> 00:10:09,810
Tian!

96
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:11,870
[Operating Room]

97
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,819
Doctor Kit! Your nephew is in your hands!

98
00:10:21,819 --> 00:10:23,074
Okay.

99
00:10:23,074 --> 00:10:26,090
Please help! Please take care of him, P'Kit!

100
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:28,959
Honey...

101
00:10:28,959 --> 00:10:30,217
Ai' Kit is excellent.

102
00:10:30,218 --> 00:10:32,009
Trust in his skills.

103
00:10:32,010 --> 00:10:33,643
Don't worry.

104
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:44,066
I'm so worried.

105
00:10:47,546 --> 00:10:53,938
In the past...that Tian has always been strong all along.

106
00:10:55,146 --> 00:11:00,214
We, too...must stay strong like our son too.

107
00:11:07,226 --> 00:11:08,361
Please stay calm.

108
00:11:08,362 --> 00:11:11,033
Right now Tian's condition is still critical.

109
00:11:11,034 --> 00:11:14,617
This is due to the chronic inflammation of his heart for many years.

110
00:11:14,618 --> 00:11:18,306
And right now, he's prone to heart failure too.

111
00:11:18,306 --> 00:11:23,879
The best option right now is that we have to quickly operate for a heart transplant.

112
00:11:23,879 --> 00:11:30,179
And the important thing is... there still isn't any matching heart from any of the donors yet.

113
00:11:30,179 --> 00:11:32,309
I've notified the Organ Donation Center already.

114
00:11:32,310 --> 00:11:34,060
But there's no response yet.

115
00:11:35,210 --> 00:11:36,586
Just take my heart, P'Kit.

116
00:11:36,587 --> 00:11:38,069
Just take my heart!

117
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:39,890
- Just go and take my heart!
-Honey, calm down.

118
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:41,250
Just take Mom's!

119
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:42,829
-Just take it!
-Honey! Honey!
- Calm down. Please calm down.

120
00:11:42,829 --> 00:11:45,805
- Just take it, P' Kit! Just take it!
- Honey! Honey!

121
00:11:45,807 --> 00:11:49,712
Doctor? There's a call from the Organ Donation Center.

122
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,377
Let me go see first.

123
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:53,978
Stay calm, alright?

124
00:12:02,566 --> 00:12:04,037
Scalpel.

125
00:12:04,037 --> 00:12:05,571
Here.

126
00:12:20,522 --> 00:12:22,070
Khun!

127
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:23,926
Where is this place?

128
00:12:25,090 --> 00:12:27,023
Who are you?

129
00:12:27,023 --> 00:12:28,751
Khun.

130
00:12:31,738 --> 00:12:33,418
Where'd she disappear to?

131
00:12:33,970 --> 00:12:35,503
Khun.

132
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:39,180
What are you trying to say?

133
00:12:39,706 --> 00:12:41,139
Hey!

134
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,330
I'll leave it to you, alright?

135
00:13:07,098 --> 00:13:10,094
Please breathe slowly as normal.

136
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,245
What happened to me?

137
00:13:14,245 --> 00:13:17,129
You've just undergone a heart transplant.

138
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:18,841
You're safe and stable now,

139
00:13:18,842 --> 00:13:21,529
but you still need to stay in bed and rest, alright?

140
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:24,978
I'll go and inform the doctor to let him know, alright?

141
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,709
I've already tried to reach Director Wanchai,

142
00:13:53,709 --> 00:13:57,260
but his secretary said he was busy at his ministry.

143
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:00,626
Leave that matter for now.

144
00:14:02,426 --> 00:14:06,978
Or maybe we might need to...consult with Dr. Kit and see.

145
00:14:07,690 --> 00:14:10,329
But it's not good if left too long. I feel bad towards him.

146
00:14:10,330 --> 00:14:12,649
He especially helped our son jump the queue.

147
00:14:12,650 --> 00:14:15,089
That's why I'm taking everything into consideration...

148
00:14:15,090 --> 00:14:18,940
Just what won't look bad and have an adverse impact on us.

149
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:25,346
- Tian!
- Mom...

150
00:14:25,346 --> 00:14:26,185
- Dad...
- Tian!

151
00:14:26,186 --> 00:14:29,059
Tian! Are you awake now, Son? How are you feeling?

152
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:31,801
Are you thirsty? You're thirsty, right? Mom's going to get you some water, alright?

153
00:14:31,802 --> 00:14:33,652
You did really well, Son.

154
00:14:36,770 --> 00:14:39,385
Here, Son. Here. Drink it slowly, alright?

155
00:14:39,385 --> 00:14:40,998
Just a bit, Son.

156
00:14:40,998 --> 00:14:42,885
Slowly, Son. Slowly.

157
00:14:42,885 --> 00:14:45,438
Do you want more? Do you want more, dear?

158
00:14:47,270 --> 00:14:51,139
Tian! I was so frightened, Son!

159
00:14:51,139 --> 00:14:54,022
I'm not even dead yet, Mom.

160
00:15:00,406 --> 00:15:02,406
Please excuse me.

161
00:15:05,386 --> 00:15:08,318
Sir? The doctor would like to see you.

162
00:15:09,626 --> 00:15:11,359
Dad will be right back, alright?

163
00:15:16,282 --> 00:15:19,422
How are you feeling? Were you able to sleep?

164
00:15:23,830 --> 00:15:29,485
Would I be able to know... just who the donor of this heart was?

165
00:15:30,906 --> 00:15:34,014
According to the rules, you can't.

166
00:15:34,970 --> 00:15:37,620
- But I think…
- Please sleep and get plenty of rest.

167
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:40,286
That way your body can recover quickly.

168
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:45,230
They're a woman, right?

169
00:15:46,554 --> 00:15:48,474
I'm not sure.

170
00:15:49,210 --> 00:15:52,126
Do you want to get some air outside?

171
00:15:59,978 --> 00:16:03,459
Girl, tonight I'm on duty to attend a heart transplant patient.

172
00:16:03,460 --> 00:16:06,601
It's the case with the son of a high-ranking official that Dr. Kit is in charge of.

173
00:16:06,602 --> 00:16:10,249
Ah, that extremely urgent case?

174
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:15,634
Oh, right! And about that female patient, do you know how much your relative's got?

175
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:23,994
[Ms. Torfun Chareonpon
Born 21 April 2540]

176
00:16:30,714 --> 00:16:32,270
Hello.

177
00:16:32,270 --> 00:16:34,060
-Thank you.
[Sangthong Aid Foundation]

178
00:16:48,362 --> 00:16:50,165
- Hey, Nong Fun.
- Yes?

179
00:16:50,165 --> 00:16:51,529
It's better if I take it for you.

180
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:53,189
A selfie like that is difficult.

181
00:16:53,189 --> 00:16:55,006
Oh, alright.

182
00:16:55,578 --> 00:16:56,537
Do I look good yet?

183
00:16:56,538 --> 00:16:58,469
You do.

184
00:16:58,469 --> 00:17:00,154
Let me do a composition really quick.

185
00:17:02,170 --> 00:17:06,397
Oh, Nong Fun! The camera. The camera's this way. Look right into the camera.

186
00:17:06,397 --> 00:17:08,229
P' Mor, just do like...a candid.

187
00:17:08,229 --> 00:17:09,289
Like a candid.

188
00:17:09,290 --> 00:17:11,119
- A candid?
- Yeah.

189
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:14,866
Sure. A candid, right? Just a moment, alright?

190
00:17:22,762 --> 00:17:24,981
Smiling this much...

191
00:17:24,981 --> 00:17:26,805
Maybe it's not candid then.

192
00:17:26,805 --> 00:17:28,709
Ai' Phu!

193
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:31,440
- P' Mor!
- There's someone that wants to take a picture with you, man.

194
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:36,750
Torfun wants a picture with you.

195
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:41,240
Uh... get closer. Get a bit closer, a bit closer.

196
00:17:41,242 --> 00:17:43,449
The camera frame is small.

197
00:17:43,450 --> 00:17:45,000
Are we close yet?

198
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:48,249
Is this okay?

199
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:52,149
Woah. It has such a great composition.

200
00:17:52,149 --> 00:17:53,577
Beautiful.

201
00:17:53,578 --> 00:17:57,338
One, two, three!

202
00:18:00,730 --> 00:18:02,713
Hey, Mor. Let me see.

203
00:18:02,714 --> 00:18:04,514
It hasn't developed yet.

204
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:10,169
Let me see it first.

205
00:18:10,170 --> 00:18:11,618
Give it here!

206
00:18:12,450 --> 00:18:15,009
I hope your girlfriend doesn't love you.

207
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:17,118
What the hell...

208
00:18:37,410 --> 00:18:39,043
Chief!

209
00:19:02,394 --> 00:19:06,354
If I had just come down and given her a ride myself...this probably wouldn't have happened.

210
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:11,538
Chief, don't blame yourself.

211
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:16,200
She's resting in peace now, man.

212
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:21,514
Yeah, I know.

213
00:19:21,514 --> 00:19:23,881
I'm just pissed at the person who did it.

214
00:19:23,882 --> 00:19:27,034
This kind of thing...nobody intended for it to happen, man.

215
00:19:27,706 --> 00:19:30,500
The other party also said that it was an accident.

216
00:19:33,540 --> 00:19:37,162
Having money can settle everything. Easy isn't it?

217
00:19:41,258 --> 00:19:44,281
I'll never forgive the person who did it.

218
00:19:44,282 --> 00:19:46,362
Come on, Phu...

219
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:54,282
[Five months later]

220
00:20:06,026 --> 00:20:08,026
- Here, Son. Of course.
- Thank you, Mom.

221
00:20:08,650 --> 00:20:12,249
Mom. Actually, you don't need to always keep an eye on me.

222
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:14,217
I'm not a bedridden patient.

223
00:20:14,218 --> 00:20:17,833
Well, I'm just afraid that you won't do as the doctor tells you to.

224
00:20:17,834 --> 00:20:21,285
Today, you were able to walk longer and you didn't pant as much as yesterday either.

225
00:20:21,285 --> 00:20:23,161
On a scale of 1 to 10, how exhausted are you?

226
00:20:23,162 --> 00:20:25,289
- Around five.
- Five?

227
00:20:25,289 --> 00:20:27,976
Is "five" risky? Or should we reduce the amount he walks?

228
00:20:27,977 --> 00:20:29,410
Mom.

229
00:20:29,914 --> 00:20:32,329
Or maybe...should we take a break from it for one day?

230
00:20:32,330 --> 00:20:34,553
Mom. That's enough...

231
00:20:34,554 --> 00:20:38,024
Actually, I recommend that you keep doing this regularly every day.

232
00:20:38,025 --> 00:20:39,494
The walking distance may be reduced.

233
00:20:39,494 --> 00:20:43,081
Apart from that, it's just a matter of taking the medications on time.

234
00:20:43,082 --> 00:20:44,569
Please don't skip any medications, alright?

235
00:20:44,570 --> 00:20:46,329
Listen to her. Alright, Son?

236
00:20:46,330 --> 00:20:51,257
It's so fortunate that Khun Tian was able to receive a matching heart in time.

237
00:20:51,258 --> 00:20:53,845
Something like this is really called a miracle.

238
00:20:53,845 --> 00:20:55,626
- Yes.
- "A miracle"?

239
00:20:58,362 --> 00:21:01,121
Wait, wait, Tian. Where are you going, Son?

240
00:21:01,121 --> 00:21:02,966
I'm going to go to the bathroom.

241
00:21:04,010 --> 00:21:05,443
Alright.

242
00:21:25,020 --> 00:21:28,565
Ai' Tian! I'm really happy to be able to hear your voice, man.

243
00:21:28,565 --> 00:21:30,445
Being home is so damn boring.

244
00:21:30,445 --> 00:21:33,161
Well, damn. It's because you haven't updated shit.

245
00:21:33,162 --> 00:21:36,389
If I were to type "R.I.P." on your Facebook,

246
00:21:36,390 --> 00:21:40,825
Dude, would you believe me that either way, everyone would believe that you actually died already.

247
00:21:40,825 --> 00:21:43,705
Well, I don't know either. I don't feel like doing anything.

248
00:21:43,706 --> 00:21:45,397
Do you want me to go see you then?

249
00:21:45,397 --> 00:21:46,841
Hey, no need.

250
00:21:46,842 --> 00:21:48,321
I was actually just thinking of going outside to see you.

251
00:21:48,321 --> 00:21:51,209
Being home, my mom keeps following me around.

252
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:53,465
Have you completely recovered already to come see me?

253
00:21:53,466 --> 00:21:56,317
Well, it's enough anyway. I'm able to go there and scold you anyway.

254
00:21:56,317 --> 00:21:59,801
There it is. Then invite your mom to come out with you, dude.

255
00:21:59,802 --> 00:22:01,753
Then why don't you invite your Pops out too then?

256
00:22:01,754 --> 00:22:04,469
Hmm...then this must mean my friend is fully recovered for sure.

257
00:22:04,470 --> 00:22:06,890
- Hey, see you later, dude.
- See you, man.

258
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:13,414
- Come on friends!
- Cheers!

259
00:22:16,086 --> 00:22:17,386
Hey, guys. What's up?

