511
00:41:43,866 --> 00:41:46,745
You just need to be interested in the fact that you received another chance at life. That's all.

512
00:41:46,746 --> 00:41:50,383
Tian, think of it as a miracle that you were able to live once again.

513
00:41:50,383 --> 00:41:52,914
Just that is enough. Alright, Son?

514
00:41:58,522 --> 00:42:01,194
Miss Torfun Chareonpon,

515
00:42:02,762 --> 00:42:06,562
a volunteer teacher at Sangthong Foundation.

516
00:42:23,380 --> 00:42:26,281
After having to walk carefully for such a long period,

517
00:42:26,282 --> 00:42:30,057
in the end, the wood flooring in this house has finally been fixed.

518
00:42:30,058 --> 00:42:33,305
Me and the villagers were so tired that we were completely out of energy.

519
00:42:33,306 --> 00:42:35,833
But the kids seemed to have a really great time.

520
00:42:35,834 --> 00:42:38,774
Ayi also said that tomorrow he'd come by tomorrow to help continue fixing the stairs.

521
00:42:38,775 --> 00:42:40,505
They're truly so sweet.

522
00:42:40,506 --> 00:42:46,483
I'm so grateful to everyone for making this home be happier than any other home.

523
00:42:49,610 --> 00:42:55,386
I've understood the value of happiness that no amount of money can buy.

524
00:43:03,450 --> 00:43:07,770
The happiness of making my life meaningful.

525
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:17,560
I was able to eat the best sticky rice of my life.

526
00:43:25,460 --> 00:43:30,217
I used to think that such a hard mattress was impossible to sleep on.

527
00:43:30,218 --> 00:43:33,774
But actually, it wasn't really that bad.

528
00:43:35,810 --> 00:43:37,945
Things that need to get fixed...

529
00:43:37,946 --> 00:43:43,113
the bookshelf at school, the mosquito net, stocking up instant noodles.

530
00:43:43,113 --> 00:43:45,097
Things that I want to do...

531
00:43:45,098 --> 00:43:49,369
I miss Moo Krata (Thai BBQ with pork). I'm getting used to the sound of tokay geckos.

532
00:43:50,778 --> 00:43:52,942
I've so much happiness.

533
00:44:10,040 --> 00:44:12,518
I've never even missed home at all.

534
00:44:13,190 --> 00:44:17,070
Wherever we feel happiness, that's the place that's home.

535
00:45:11,510 --> 00:45:13,290
Eat a lot, Son.

536
00:45:14,746 --> 00:45:15,909
Nong Ton!

537
00:45:15,909 --> 00:45:18,681
What did I say about eating at the big table with grandma?

538
00:45:18,682 --> 00:45:20,105
Do I need to take it away?

539
00:45:20,106 --> 00:45:24,777
Put it down first, honey. Your eyes will get ruined. Grandma already told you that. Eat first.

540
00:45:24,778 --> 00:45:27,749
Tum. I told you not to play with your food.

541
00:45:27,749 --> 00:45:30,153
Otherwise, you don't need to play games anymore.

542
00:45:30,154 --> 00:45:33,241
I don't want to eat Chinese broccoli. I want to eat sausage.

543
00:45:33,242 --> 00:45:35,973
Eat it for now. I'll P' Miang fry some for you tomorrow.

544
00:45:35,973 --> 00:45:39,049
Don't want to! I want to eat it today! I want to eat it! I want to eat it!

545
00:45:39,049 --> 00:45:41,019
- Calm down. Calm down, sweetie.
- Hey, I've explained it. Eat it for now.

546
00:45:41,019 --> 00:45:44,710
- I want to eat it today. Mom, why won't you fry it?
- Miang will fry it for you tomorrow. Eat this for today.

547
00:45:44,710 --> 00:45:47,304
- Eat it for now.
- Tum, calm down, sweetie.
- Here. Here.

548
00:45:47,304 --> 00:45:49,433
- Eat it.
- Yay!

549
00:45:55,434 --> 00:45:57,429
So he'll quiet down.

550
00:45:57,429 --> 00:45:59,163
Isn't it good?

551
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:05,142
Go ahead and eat up.

552
00:46:07,338 --> 00:46:09,470
I think that I'm full already.

553
00:46:16,154 --> 00:46:17,353
Mom.

554
00:46:17,354 --> 00:46:18,689
Let me kiss your cheek once.

555
00:46:18,690 --> 00:46:22,358
Hey, why are you giving kisses at the dining table?

556
00:46:26,602 --> 00:46:28,035
Dad.

557
00:46:28,570 --> 00:46:30,920
Don't forget to take your medicine after meals.

558
00:46:35,194 --> 00:46:37,044
I'll be leaving first, Je.

559
00:46:43,962 --> 00:46:46,512
Are you happy now, getting that sausage?

560
00:47:14,682 --> 00:47:16,393
You don't need to worry about me.

561
00:47:16,394 --> 00:47:18,049
You don't need to search after me.

562
00:47:18,050 --> 00:47:22,366
Whenever I'm ready, I'll come back on my own. Tian.

563
00:48:51,090 --> 00:48:53,700
[Torfun Chareonpon]

564
00:48:58,320 --> 00:49:00,360
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

565
00:49:04,370 --> 00:49:08,098
I've finally arrived...the village of Pha Pun Dao (Cliff of A Thousand Stars).

566
00:49:12,854 --> 00:49:15,017
It can said to be absurd, but whatever...

567
00:49:15,018 --> 00:49:19,302
The Pha Pun Dao tale could be true.

568
00:49:19,302 --> 00:49:21,717
If I ever have a chance...

569
00:49:21,717 --> 00:49:25,409
Well, whatever,...at least I know that I've tried.

570
00:49:25,410 --> 00:49:29,799
On the last night of the year, if I ever finish counting to one thousand stars…

571
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:31,500
What the hell does this mean?

572
00:49:55,870 --> 00:49:59,080
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

573
00:50:37,466 --> 00:50:38,899
Khru Tian!

574
00:50:39,946 --> 00:50:41,409
Are you Khru Tian?

575
00:50:41,410 --> 00:50:43,358
This way, sir!

576
00:50:44,858 --> 00:50:46,586
Come on over!

577
00:50:48,410 --> 00:50:49,849
- Wow! Hello, Khru!
- Hello.

578
00:50:49,849 --> 00:50:51,012
- Khru Tian, right?
- Yes.

579
00:50:51,012 --> 00:50:53,545
- Okay. Let's go. Get in the car first.
- Sure.

580
00:50:53,545 --> 00:50:55,756
This way. Here.

581
00:50:56,950 --> 00:50:58,570
Yes, sir.
[For complaints call 1584]

582
00:51:02,970 --> 00:51:04,503
Let's go!

583
00:51:07,300 --> 00:51:10,879
The weather has gotten really nice here in Chiang Mai, right?

584
00:51:10,879 --> 00:51:13,861
Oh! It's getting good now, I'm telling you.

585
00:51:13,861 --> 00:51:15,950
Let's go!

586
00:51:27,030 --> 00:51:29,477
I'm Yod.

587
00:51:29,477 --> 00:51:32,370
Or you can call me Chang Yod if you'd like.
[T/N: "Chang" means "technician", "mechanic", "engineer", or "repairman"]

588
00:51:32,900 --> 00:51:36,869
Well, Khama asked me to pick you up, Khru.

589
00:51:36,869 --> 00:51:38,703
Khama?

590
00:51:38,703 --> 00:51:44,726
Oh! Khama here is, well, the village chief.

591
00:51:44,726 --> 00:51:47,737
You'll be able to meet him today, Khru.

592
00:51:47,738 --> 00:51:49,271
Alright.

593
00:51:53,018 --> 00:51:56,120
Well, Khru... Can I ask you a bit of a question?

594
00:51:57,068 --> 00:52:00,441
Why did someone like you choose to teach in Pha Pun Dao, Khru?

595
00:52:00,442 --> 00:52:02,874
It's such an impoverished area.

596
00:52:03,890 --> 00:52:09,097
Only once in a while would I say that there'd ever be a teacher that would want to teach here.

597
00:52:09,098 --> 00:52:13,477
So Khru, are you here to search for a meaning or search for some sort of answer?

598
00:52:13,477 --> 00:52:18,505
Because... the previous teachers from before also mentioned that to me.

599
00:52:18,506 --> 00:52:20,656
Well, I came to be a teacher of course, Chang.

600
00:52:21,546 --> 00:52:23,426
Ah, right.

601
00:52:24,520 --> 00:52:26,762
And here I was asking.

602
00:52:28,760 --> 00:52:31,759
And the others that came here, they came searching for meaning...

603
00:52:31,759 --> 00:52:33,730
Well, were they able to find it?

604
00:52:34,370 --> 00:52:39,321
"Meaning"? Regarding this, I'm not sure either, Khru.

605
00:52:39,322 --> 00:52:44,350
Because for the most part, they'd run away before they would, Khru.

606
00:52:45,722 --> 00:52:51,770
Oh! But there was a previous teacher before you that stayed for a while.

607
00:53:00,570 --> 00:53:02,777
Oh, here, here. Here, Khru.

608
00:53:02,778 --> 00:53:05,779
Eat this for now. That way you'll have energy.

609
00:53:05,779 --> 00:53:07,113
Thank you, Chang.

610
00:53:07,114 --> 00:53:11,625
Yeah, for today I'm going to warn you that you'll be exhausted for sure, Khru.

611
00:53:11,626 --> 00:53:13,241
And another thing I should tell you...

612
00:53:13,242 --> 00:53:16,592
You can't find something like this to eat at Pha Pun Dao.

613
00:53:19,240 --> 00:53:21,974
Go ahead. Eat. Fill up your strength.

614
00:53:23,270 --> 00:53:26,690
Hey, Ai Tao (Old Gray)! Hey! Hey!

615
00:53:37,290 --> 00:53:42,366
Ai Tao, really! Just great! You old junk.

616
00:53:45,318 --> 00:53:46,851
Oh, wow.

617
00:53:48,330 --> 00:53:50,486
It's not what I think, right?

618
00:53:52,414 --> 00:53:54,642
Would you able to walk, Khru?

619
00:53:56,218 --> 00:53:58,740
It's just maybe 3 kilometers away.

620
00:54:07,640 --> 00:54:11,565
Khru, have you ever been to Chiang Mai before?

621
00:54:11,565 --> 00:54:13,642
Well, I've been here a few times.

622
00:54:14,370 --> 00:54:17,379
The Pha Pun Dao village of ours,

623
00:54:17,379 --> 00:54:19,705
well it's on the border,

624
00:54:19,706 --> 00:54:24,129
if you cross over just a bit, then it'd be our neighboring country, right?

625
00:54:24,130 --> 00:54:30,322
As for our villagers, there are some hill tribes people as well as Thai people mixed in.

626
00:54:30,330 --> 00:54:33,145
But the language used here is still Thai.
[T/N: N. Thailand has 7 main hill tribes like Karen & Hmong. They have their own languages, cultures, and customs.]

627
00:54:33,146 --> 00:54:35,886
Therefore you don't have to worry at all, Khru.

628
00:54:36,450 --> 00:54:39,766
And...is this place scary, Chang?

629
00:54:41,890 --> 00:54:44,745
It is an area that's considered a red zone, Khru.

630
00:54:44,746 --> 00:54:50,642
Most villages here have military and border patrol police help keep an eye.

631
00:54:51,320 --> 00:54:52,869
As for Pha Pun Dao…

632
00:54:52,870 --> 00:54:56,313
It has our group to come in and help monitor.

633
00:54:56,314 --> 00:54:59,225
Because the government has too much on its plate.

634
00:54:59,226 --> 00:55:01,449
They're not able to look after us and not able to do it thoroughly.

635
00:55:01,450 --> 00:55:03,786
So we have to be their eyes and ears.

636
00:55:03,787 --> 00:55:07,502
If you look at it, we even look more stern than the military officers.

637
00:55:11,450 --> 00:55:14,117
Especially my supervisor, Chief Phu.

638
00:55:14,117 --> 00:55:18,970
I'll tell you now, anyone who sees him mistakes him for a military officer.

639
00:55:20,170 --> 00:55:23,138
But in actuality, he's kind.

640
00:55:24,310 --> 00:55:27,502
So is he stern or kind exactly, Chang?

641
00:55:30,230 --> 00:55:32,330
You'll find out soon, Khru.

642
00:55:38,950 --> 00:55:41,100
Are you still able to do it, Khru?

643
00:55:41,100 --> 00:55:42,517
I can still go on, Chang.

644
00:55:42,517 --> 00:55:45,406
It's only a bit further. Come on!

645
00:55:51,094 --> 00:55:53,266
We're almost there, Khru.

646
00:55:54,790 --> 00:55:59,490
Right there. It's that one. That's your house, Khru.

647
00:56:05,594 --> 00:56:09,506
Chief, this is Khru Tian, the new volunteer teacher.

648
00:56:23,178 --> 00:56:25,211
Khun!

649
00:56:26,960 --> 00:56:30,950
[Phupha Viriyanon]

650
00:56:58,722 --> 00:57:05,190
[Directed by Noppharnach Chaiwimol]

651
00:57:27,346 --> 00:57:28,979
Khun.

652
00:57:38,074 --> 00:57:40,314
My name is Phupha.

653
00:57:40,314 --> 00:57:42,656
But calling me "Chief" would be better.

654
00:57:44,218 --> 00:57:45,977
Being this weak,

655
00:57:45,978 --> 00:57:48,665
If you can't live here, then quickly tell me.

656
00:57:48,666 --> 00:57:50,766
So that I can find a ride to send you back.

657
00:58:00,202 --> 00:58:02,529
Thank you for your concern,

658
00:58:02,530 --> 00:58:06,574
but I can stay here, and I probably won't leave anytime soon.

659
00:58:17,734 --> 00:58:21,245
And another thing, my name is Tian.

660
00:58:21,245 --> 00:58:25,078
In case you want to know me, Chief.

661
00:58:27,320 --> 00:58:31,129
This house is housing for the volunteer teacher.

662
00:58:31,130 --> 00:58:33,289
At night, there's no electricity to use.

663
00:58:33,290 --> 00:58:35,225
There's no phone signal.

664
00:58:35,226 --> 00:58:37,276
Are you sure you can live here?

665
00:58:39,050 --> 00:58:43,126
If others can live here, then why can't I?

666
00:59:09,018 --> 00:59:10,768
How stuck up.

667
00:59:35,994 --> 00:59:37,827
Shit! It's hot! Hey!

668
00:59:45,066 --> 00:59:46,697
Help! Help!

669
00:59:46,698 --> 00:59:48,249
Help!

670
00:59:48,250 --> 00:59:49,830
Help!

671
00:59:50,750 --> 00:59:52,483
Khun!

672
01:00:02,390 --> 01:00:04,540
What exactly are you doing?

673
01:00:05,220 --> 01:00:06,953
I'm helping you, of course.

674
01:00:13,882 --> 01:00:16,780
And if it's all wet like this, how am I supposed to sleep?

675
01:00:24,058 --> 01:00:26,041
You can not sleep if you'd like...

676
01:00:26,042 --> 01:00:28,457
But tomorrow, you have lessons at 8 o'clock.

677
01:00:28,458 --> 01:00:30,191
Don't be late.

678
01:00:40,263 --> 01:00:45,249
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

679
01:00:45,250 --> 01:00:47,169
[Preview]
Guys, this is the new teacher.

680
01:00:47,169 --> 01:00:51,329
Khru Seetian, you wrote and switched the letters "Do-Dek" and "To-Tao".

681
01:00:51,329 --> 01:00:56,949
Me and Ai Rang here believe that either way you'll win the hearts of the villagers for sure, Khru.

682
01:00:56,949 --> 01:00:59,145
The people here all bathe right here.

683
01:00:59,146 --> 01:01:02,549
Are you able to bathe here? Or do you need me to take you down into the city to bathe?

684
01:01:02,550 --> 01:01:05,293
Let me seriously ask you... Is there anything you can actually do?

685
01:01:05,293 --> 01:01:08,490
Come here. It's like this.

686
01:01:10,890 --> 01:01:17,310
♫ The story that's been told however many times is still the same ♫

687
01:01:17,310 --> 01:01:23,810
♫ It's that I love you, love you. It has never changed ♫

688
01:01:23,810 --> 01:01:30,290
♫ If perhaps the stars hear the words of the prayers within my heart ♫

689
01:01:30,290 --> 01:01:41,280
♫ No matter how many thousands of times, I'll still ask for my heart to be near you ♫

